1:- What are the benifits of using css?
Ans:- 1 css on of the most benifits of css is its ability to separate content from presentation.

      2 This separation enhances the maintainability of web pages as changes to the styling can be made without altering the underlying html structure.

      3 css enables consistent styling across an entire website or multiple pages

      4 This is one of the many advantage of using css

      5 css you can crate responsive web designs that adapt to diffrent screen sizes and devices this is another main one among advantage of cascading style sheet.

      6 Modifying the appearance of a website is more straightforward with css

      7 External css files can be linked to multiple web pages,making it easy to apply consistent styling across an entire website.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
      
2:- What are the disadvantages of CSS?
Ans:-  1) Browser Compatibility
       2) Learning Curve
       3) Limited Layout Control
       4) Lack of Security
       5) Performance impact
       6) Overriding Styles
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3:- What is the difference between CSS2 and CSS3 ?
Ans:-   
                         CSS2                                                                             
css splits up different sections of the code into modules

css2 only web safe fonts can be used

css2 the concept of simple selectors were present

css2 Doesn't support the Border-Box property

                         CSS3
css ad html were put into a single file,there was no concept of modules before

css3 special fonts can be used such as those in google fonts and typecast

css3 the selectors were called as a sequence of simple selectors.com

css3 support the Border-Box property

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4:- Name a few CSS style components
Ans:- The three parts to a css style :selector,property and value

selector is the html tag you are formating (h1) selector id,class name.
property is the atttribute you want to change font,color,background-color,border,textalign etc..
values each property is set ot a value value are separated by a colon(:).
