7:-How can image repetition of the backup be controlled?
Ans:- Controlled repetition image background-repeat property the background-repeat property in css is used to repeat the background image both horizontally and vertically. it also decides whether the background image will be repeated or not

background-repeat:repeat|repeat-x|repeat-y|no-repeat
Example of Background Image controlled

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Background Repeat</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-image: url(https://images.pexels.com/photos/1687944/pexels-photo-1687944.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=600);
            background-repeat: no-repeat;
        }

        p {
            color: red;
            font-size: 5.8rem;
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet.</p>
</body>

</html>

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

8:- What is the use of the background-position property ?
Ans:-Background poistion use of the property sets the starting position of a background image.background image by default placed at the top-left corner of element and repeated both vertically and horizontally.

            background-position:left;
            background-position:top;
            background-position:center;
            background-position:25% 75%;
            background-position:right 35% bottom 45%;

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <title>Background Repeat</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-image: url("https://images.pexels.com/photos/1687944/pexels-photo-1687944.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=600");
            padding: 300px;
            background-repeat: no-repeat;
            background-position: right 35% bottom 45%;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
</body>
</html>

