13:- what are the ways to integrate CSS as a web page?
Ans:- css may be added to html in three diffrent ways.to style a single html element on the page,use inline css in astyle attribute.by adding css to the head section of our html document we can embed an internal stylesheet.we can also connect to an external stylesheet that separates our css from our html

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

14:- what is embedded style sheets?
Ans:- embeddes style sheet in css allows you to define styles for entire html document in one place. it s way to encapsulate your styling rules within the document itself.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <title>Page Title</title>
    <!-- Embedded stylesheet -->
    <style>
        h2{
            font-size:1.5rem;
            color:red;
            text-align:center;
        }

        p{
            font-variant:italic;
        }

    </style>

</head>
<body>
    <h3>Welcome To Html</h3>
    <p>This is document is uisng an embedded stylesheet</p>
    <p>This is a paragraph</p>

</body>
</html>
    



--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

15:- what are the external style sheets?
Ans:- External style sheet is a separate css file that can be accessed by creating a link within the head section of the webpage. multiple webpages can use the same link to access the stylesheet.the link to an external style sheet is placed within the head section of the page.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

16:- what are the advantages and disadvantages of using external style sheet?
Ans:- Advantage of css 
      it is easier to update whole site
      Better Website Speed
      Easier to maintain
      consistent Design
    ------------------------------------------
      Disadvantages

      cross-browser issues
      security issues
      extra work for developers
    ------------------------------------------

